<TEXT>
prison terms of 900 years each were 
recommended wednesday for two men convicted in connection with the 
torture slaying of us drug agent enrique camarena who died 
working undercover in mexico 
federal prosecutors also recommended in a sentencing memorandum 
filed wednesday that one of the defendants raul lopez alvarez be 
given an additional 10 years and that both men be ineligible for 
parole for 60 years 
the recommendation for jesus felix gutierrez a third man 
convicted in the case is 10 years 
lopez 29 a former mexican homicide detective stationed in 
guadalajara was convicted in september of the 1985 murders of the 
drug enforcement administration agent and pilot alfredo zavala 
avelar 
lopez also was found guilty of conspiracy to kidnap kidnapping 
accessory after the fact and two counts of committing violent acts 
in support of racketeering a new statute aimed at drugrelated 
crimes 
rene verdugo urquidez 36 an admitted drug trafficker also was 
convicted last month of five counts of conspiracy kidnapping 
murder and two counts of violent acts in support of racketeering 
sentencing for lopez is scheduled for monday and verdugos is 
scheduled for wednesday 
felix 39 is serving 15 years in jail for a drug trafficking 
conviction he was found guilty of being an accessory after the 
fact by helping the alleged mastermind of the scheme rafael caro 
quintero escape to costa rica following the murders 
caro quintero is in custody in mexico serving a sentence for 
weapons violations he has been tried in the camarena slaying but 
authorities there have not yet reached a verdict sentencing for 
felix also was scheduled wednesday 
