taiwanese soldiers stranded on the mainland after 
the communist victory of 1949 have formed an organization to 
further their demand that they be allowed to return to taiwan 
the return home association represents about 1000 taiwanborn 
veterans both of han and gaoshan nationality who were left on the 
mainland when the defeated nationalists fled to taiwan in 1949 the 
official china daily said today 
the daily said the nongovernmental organization will urge the 
taiwan government to ease restrictions and allow them to return 
home to reunite with their relatives 
it quoted xu zhaolin president of the association as saying it 
would negotiate directly with agencies of taiwan in third countries 
and regions 
the nationalist government in 1987 removed restrictions on 
travel to the mainland and more than 150000 residents of taiwan 
have since traveled to china to visit relatives sightsee and 
conduct business however the nationalists have not made a final 
decision on whether mainland residents can visit taiwan 
