the head of swedens police force has 
resigned after heavy criticism of his role in an unauthorized 
investigation into the 1986 slaying of prime minister olof palme 
national police chief nilserik ahmansson told reporters 
wednesday that he decided to step down after attorney general hans 
stark said ahmansson had been too passive and had given an 
outsider access to classified police files concerning the palme 
case 
justice minister annagreta leijon resigned under pressure last 
june after disclosures of her role in the unauthorized 
investigation 
leijon admitted helping ebbe carlsson a publisher with close 
connections to the governing social democratic party run a private 
probe of the palme murder 
an associate of carlsson has been charged with smuggling illegal 
wiretapping equipment into sweden for the probe 
last summer ahmansson leijon and carlsson testified on 
national television before parliaments constitutional committee 
about their roles in the affair 
palme was shot feb 28 in downtown stockholm the killer is 
still at large authorities have offered a 77 million reward for 
information leading to his capture 
