the presidential election is more than two 
weeks away but insiders already are predicting that a george bush 
administration would be run by a cast of familiar figures from 
ronald reagans presidency 
with michael dukakis far down in the polls and struggling to 
recover his staff says transition planning is on hold even so 
democrats who have been out of power for eight years dream about 
the makeup of a dukakis administration 
among republicans there is a general expectation that former 
treasury secretary james a baker iii who is bushs campaign 
chairman would become secretary of state former sen john tower 
of texas an arms negotiator for reagan and an adviser to bush on 
national security matters has been lobbying for secretary of 
defense and probably has a claim on it republicans say 
gop sources say dick thornburgh who replaced edwin meese iii as 
attorney general this year probably would remain as head of the 
justice department while nicholas brady a onetime bush campaign 
adviser who replaced baker at treasury would hold onto his job 
other likely holdovers in a bush administration according to 
various sources are labor secretary ann dore mclaughlin and 
