outside heritage high school two raised a large cardboard sign 
that read spin this atwater 
spin is the word for what political operatives often do when 
talking to reporters they evaluate the current political 
situation or a given event in terms that serve their campaigns 
strategy and make their candidate look as good as possible 
spinning has a negative connotation among people who see it as 
attempted manipulation or outright deception 
lee atwater bushs campaign manager is one of the masters of 
spin 
atwater who does not generally travel with the campaign 
happened to be on the road with bush this day when a tv crew got 
the sign and showed it to him he laughed and seemed quite pleased 
at the acknowledgement of his speciality 
he later raised the sign aloft in the press bus while asking if 
anyone had any questions and continued the days spinning in the 
campaign plane later with the sign perched atop his seat 
</TEXT>
