the dismissal of ethnic albanian leaders it announced plans for 
street protests and urged slavic members of the kosovo leadership 
to resign as an example and protest 
milosevic told a crowd of workers in a belgrade industrial 
suburb only the serbian party had the right to decide whether his 
ally ckrebic should resign from the national politburo 
stipe suvar chief of the national party said loss of a 
conference vote by a politburo member was unprecedented 
party leaders from other regions have been angered by 
milosevics support of nationalist rallies by serbs and suspect 
him of seeking greater power at their expense 
parliaments relaxation of the austerity program allows raises 
of 140152 percent for workers in profitable enterprises and in 
social services like health and education 
the changes were approved by the international monetary fund 
which demanded the austerity program as a condition for helping 
yugoslavia deal with its 21 billion foreign debt 
