food clothing and medical supplies approved by congress last 
month they have received no weaponry from the united states since 
lethal aid was halted in february 
though congress has been strongly opposed to new military aid 
the bill says a sandinista failure to comply with central american 
peace accords will inevitably cause the congress to approve 
additional military assistance for the nicaraguan resistance 
the wilderness bill affects more than 6 million acres of montana 
and is the result of a compromise worked out among competing 
interests including conservationists and the timber and lumber 
industries 
the bill designates about 143 million acres of forest service 
land as wilderness 360000 acres as special management areas and 
another 20000 acres as federal study areas it also releases for 
nonwilderness uses more than 10 million acres in montanas 10 
national forests 
