the difference in the two readings could be regarded as 
insignificant 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude thus a reading of 45 reflects an earthquake 10 times 
stronger than one of 35the san francisco earthquake of 1906 
which occurred before the richter scale was devised has been 
estimated at 83 
