the leftist government enacted a 
30day state of emergency thursday that restricts civil liberties 
and unauthorizes storm news in order to prepare for a hurricane 
heading toward nicaragua 
the announcement of the presidential decree came as hurricane 
joan lumbered in the caribbean with 105 mph winds more than 200 
miles from the nicaraguan coastal town of bluefields 
nicaragua has been under a state of emergency for most of the 
nine years that the sandinista government has been been in control 
the sandinistas first imposed restrictions on civil liberties in 
1982 shortly after a war with usbacked rebels known as contras 
intensified that law was revoked in january in keeping with a 
central american peace plan 
however the measures issued thursday were weaker than earlier 
ones that barred freedom of movement and granted police 
wideranging powers 
instead they deal mainly with the press they prohibit all mass 
media from publishing or broadcsting news on the storm unless it 
was provided by the presidency or authorized sources 
the law signed by president daniel ortega said the government 
could temporarily commandeer vehicles if needed to fight the 
effects of the hurricane 
