that manufactures oreo cookies and winston cigarettes underscored 
the soaring interest in food companies and wellknown brand names 
it came just three days after philip morris cos inc offered to 
buy processed foods manufacturer kraft inc for 11 billion and two 
days after pillsbury co rejected a 523 billion bid from the 
british firm grand metropolitan plc 
wall street apparently expected a higher offer for rjr nabisco 
