verity spoke to the joint meetings of the southeast united 
statesjapan association and its japanese counterpart the 
japansoutheast united states association the groups work to 
foster better business ties between japan and the southeast 
speaking with reporters later verity said if were going to 
reduce the trade imbalance we have to increase exports to japan 
im convinced we can ease that trade imbalance in the next three to 
four years 
verity called the deficit a cancer on this society and 
warned american producers will not be able to survive as long as 
they only depend on the us market 
asked about democrat michael dukakis prediction that he will 
eliminate the trade deficit in four years verity said the only way 
that could be done is by putting up trade barriers or by a 
recession 
verity said the american people dont want either and are 
willing to see a gradual cut in the trade deficit as exports grow 
during his speech verity noted progress has been made in easing 
the trade imbalance with recent agreements that allow american 
companies more access to japanese construction projects and the new 
omnibus trade bill 
he said the measure should not cause any problem for trade 
between the two nations 
it will be administered in a very enlightened way and japan 
has nothing to fear from that trade bill he said 
to ease the trade deficit he said steps need to be taken to 
change the old japanese product distribution system a system 
which for imports often double or triples the price of the 
product before it gets to the consumer 
verity a resident of beaufort sc said a recent trade 
mission to japan showed that there are markets there for top 
quality american goods 
